    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Redness\nand swelling of lids and conjunctiva\nOcular pain\nor foreign body sensation\nDecreased visual acuity\n(if located in central visual axis or uveal tract is inflamed)\nPhotophobia\nGray/white corneal lesion (will have fluorescein uptake)\nRequires careful physical exam as 40% of lesions < 5mm\nHypopyon\nmay be present\nIritis\nsigns may be present (miotic pupil, consensual photophobia)",
      "subsections": {
        "Complications": {
          "text": "Corneal scarring\nCorneal perforation\nAnterior/posterior synechiae\nGlaucoma\nCataracts",
